TEAM - The CardLinx Association














































 











 



























  













   THE CARDLINX ASSOCIATION TEAM    











  













   THE CARDLINX ASSOCIATION TEAM    














 Board Members





































				Silvio Tavares			




				President and Founding Chief Executive Officer			




			READ SILVIO'S BIO		

Silvio Tavares is an experienced CEO, senior executive and thought leader with over 15 years of experience in the digital commerce and payments industry. Mr. Tavares is President and CEO of The CardLinx Association, a leading global trade association for the payments and digital advertising industries. CardLinx founding members include MasterCard, Discover, First Data, Facebook and Microsoft among others.
He was previously SVP and Global Head of Information Products at Visa Inc. where he led a business unit generating several hundred million dollars in annual sales and successfully launched key new industry leading products in the areas of payment fraud detection, digital marketing and merchant loyalty. Mr. Tavares joined Visa from First Data, where he was Senior Vice President and Global Head of Information and Analytics. At First Data, he patented and launched First Data’s U.S. macro-economic spending indicator. He began his career at AT&T where he authored one of the earliest business method patents for web-based payments. He has authored over fifteen granted or pending patents in the fields of digital commerce, electronic payments and payments analytics.
Mr. Tavares earned a Juris Doctor degree from the Boston University School of Law (Oxford University Program), an MBA from Boston College and a Bachelor of Science Degree in Electrical and Computer Engineering from Tufts University.


















				Marushka Bland			




				Board Vice President, Head of Payments Marketing			




			READ MARUSHKA'S BIO »		

Marushka Bland is the Global Director of Payments Marketing for Whole Foods Market. In this role, Marushka oversees all aspects of mobile payments, card-linked marketing, prepaid sales, gift cards and other payment promotions for Whole Foods, the world’s leader in natural and organic foods with 455 stores in North America and the United Kingdom. She is also a member of the Global Marketing and Communications Team.
Prior to Whole Foods, Marushka worked at Hello Fresh and Heidrick & Struggles. She started her career as an attorney with law firm Chadbourne & Parke. Marushka received a J.D. with honors from Emory University School of Law and a B.A. magna cum laude from the University of Pennsylvania























				Cassie Boutelle			




				Head of Loyalty Products, FIS			




			READ CASSIE'S BIO »		

Cassie Boutelle is the Vice President of Loyalty Products for FIS, the world’s largest provider of retail payments and banking technologies.
Cassie specializes in retail and financial institution loyalty products as well as emerging payment trends. Her latest efforts have been focused on the convergence of both of these areas via point of sale engagement opportunities, data sharing, coalitions, and other opportunities for partnering together to drive mutual successes. Recent accomplishments include winning PYMNTS.com 2016 POS Innovation award and Pay Before’s 2016 Outstanding Loyalty Program.
As the loyalty rewards industry continues to evolve year after year, she sees more brands and financial institutions understanding the benefits of reward programs, such as increased spend and increased consumer insight via customer data. Today’s consumers are savvier than ever and wanting more from their retailers and financial institutions, looking for more incentives to drive where they shop and which card they use. Cassie sees the opportunity in the challenge of this environment, viewing loyalty programs as ways to stay competitive and innovate, ultimately solving for utopian consumer experiences and increasing revenues.























				Jon Carder			




				CEO, Empyr			




			READ JON'S BIO »		

Jon Carder is CEO and Co-founder of Empyr, an innovative online-to-offline commerce platform providing a frictionless approach to monetizing online consumers in the offline world.
Carder is a serial entrepreneur who has been nominated for Ernst & Young’s Entrepreneur of the Year award three separate times and was previously named San Diego’s Most Influential Tech Executive. He has successfully created several multi-million Internet businesses, including card-linked offer company, Mogl, which was named Most Innovative Tech Company in San Diego. Carder also founded MojoPages, a local search engine that helps people find the best local businesses. Some of the nation’s largest media companies are using MojoPages technology including Hearst, CBS, FOX and ClearChannel.























				Ken Hirschman			




				VP of Strategic Alliances			




			READ KEN'S BIO »		

Ken Hirschman is General Manager and Vice President of in-store offers at Rakuten/Ebates.
Ken oversees multiple functions at Ebates, including business development, M&A, legal, credit card, and Ebates In-Store. At Ebates, Ken built a legal department, raised a funding round, bought six companies, founded two Asian offices, launched a de novo credit card program, quarterbacked an IPO, and negotiated the sale of Ebates to Rakuten for $1 billion.























				Eduardo Indacochea			




				General Manager of Post-Sales Monetization			




			READ EDUARDO'S BIO »		

As Microsoft’s General Manager of Post-Sales Monetization, Eduardo is responsible for growing monetization through increased user engagement across all devices within and across Microsoft’s portfolio of products and services.
Over the course of his career, Indacochea has held a variety of leadership roles in engineering, product management, strategy, marketing, and finance. Previously, he was responsible of Global Relationship Marketing of Outlook.com, OneDrive, Internet Explorer, Surface, Hotmail, and Messenger.
Before joining Microsoft in 2007, Indacochea led strategy and planning teams at Nextel Peru. Indacochea began his career as Peruvian Navy Officer. He had a number of leadership positions in engineering and communications during his tenure at the Navy.
A native of Lima, Peru; Indacochea earned a bachelor’s degree in Maritime Science from Escuela Naval del Peru, where he was appointed as Battalion Commander and awarded Sword of Honor distinction; Naval Engineering from Universidad Nacional de Ingenieria (Peru), Master of Industrial Engineering from Universidad de Lima (Peru) and an MBA Ross School of Business at University of Michigan. He is married, has two children, and lives in Kirkland, WA.























				Brandon Logsdon			




				President and Chief Executive Officer			




			READ BRANDON'S BIO »		

With over 13 years of experience at Excentus, Brandon Logsdon has been the driving force behind developing a first-of-kind, nationwide coalition program and engaging in strategic relationships with our cornerstone partners, Shell and MasterCard. In his role as CEO, Brandon is also a member of the Excentus Board of Directors, and he oversees three strategic Excentus business units – the Fuel Rewards coalition program, our subsidiary Centego, which provides enabling technology and services for private-label fuel reward programs and managing our IP portfolio. Prior to joining Excentus in 2002, Brandon worked at GTE Internetworking, JPMorgan Chase, iChoose and he was also the Co-founder and Principal at Bloomin’ Partners Inc.
Brandon holds a BA in Finance and Marketing from Texas Christian University (Go Frogs) and he is a board member for the North Texas chapter of the Folds of Honor foundation. When he’s not spending time with his wife and three children, you’ll find him making triple doubles on the court or chasing that elusive hole-in-one.























				Dale McCrory			




				Senior Vice President, Advanced Solutions and Innovation			




			READ DALE'S BIO »		

Dale McCrory is a senior leader in Card-linking Services, Loyalty and CRM innovation at First Data Corporation.
Dale McCrory is a senior leader in Card-linking Services, Loyalty and CRM innovation at First Data Corporation, where she is responsible for Strategy, Business Development, Product Development, and Commercialization. Dale has led the development of internal and external partners to launch technology solutions that drive value through the collision of Payments and Advertising. This includes enterprise offers platforms, POS integration, offer syndication and affiliate marketing, consumer segmentation and campaign analytics for Ad Sales and Advertising Publishing organizations delivering targeted marketing, CRM and loyalty solutions.
Prior to joining First Data, she was Vice President at TSYS for over 12 years, where she led several functional teams during that tenure, including Product Strategy & Development, Professional Services, Client Relationship Management, Program Analytics and Marketing, Client Conversions and Implementation and Operations. She played a critical role in the design, launch and growth of loyalty programs in the Financial Services space throughout North American, including programs for global, national and regional organizations such as Cap One, Citibank, JP Morgan Chase, Wells Fargo, Royal Bank of Scotland, Sears, and The Home Depot.























				Kirsty Rankin			




				SVP, Global Group Head, MasterCard Loyalty			




			READ KRISTY'S BIO »		

Kirsty Rankin is Senior Vice President and Global Group Head of MasterCard’s Loyalty Solutions. In this global role, she is responsible for the strategy, design and management of innovative loyalty value propositions for the merchant community. MasterCard is committed to providing tailored, leading edge loyalty solutions that help businesses drive greater engagement and create longer term more profitable customers.
Kirsty brings a wealth of loyalty knowledge and expertise having been the Co-CEO of Pinpoint Pty Ltd, one of Asia Pacific’s leading loyalty and marketing service companies with offices in Australia, China, Singapore, Hong Kong, India, Japan and Taiwan. During her 20+ year tenure at Pinpoint, Kirsty was instrumental in the growth of the company to over 500 employees where she developed highly successful, award winning loyalty and marketing programs across a broad range of industry verticals including financial services, retail, travel and entertainment. Pinpoint was acquired by MasterCard in July 2014.
Prior to Pinpoint, Kirsty worked at Qantas and American Express.
Kirsty holds a Bachelor of Commerce from the University of New South Wales where she was a University Medallist. In Australia, she was a board member of ADMA, the leading marketing and advertising association and an advisory board member for Visit California. She is currently living in California where she works out of the MasterCard Office in San Carlos.























				Arvind Ronta			




				Director, Global Head of Products – Commerce, Data, Security & Commercial Payments			




			READ ARVIND'S BIO »		

Arvind is an experienced payments executive with a breadth of consulting and industry experience, focused on driving innovation and revenue growth.
At Discover, Arvind is leading an innovation pipeline of next-generation products for card-linking, big data and consumer authentication.
Prior to joining Discover, Arvind was a consultant in the Strategy & Operations group at Deloitte Consulting LLP and led business model innovation, digital transformation and strategic initiatives for clients across the payments value chain. Prior to Discover, he managed P&L and product-marketing responsibilities for a leading global online payment processor. Arvind holds a BS in Mechanical Engineering and an MBA from Queen’s University in Canada.























Jonathan Silver 




				President and CEO			




			READ JONATHAN'S BIO »		

Bio coming soon.























				Satoru (“Sato”) Suzuki			




				General Manager and Head of US Office, Sumitomo Mitsui Card			




			READ SATORU'S BIO »		

Satoru Suzuki is General Manager of Sumitomo Mitsui Card, USA and is based in the Palo Alto Office of Sumitomo Mitsui Card. He works on research and advanced payment solutions and technologies in North America and business development. He has 20+ years career in credit card business.





























				Steven L. Van Fleet			




				President, Financial Services and CLL (Card Linked Loyalty), Augeo			




			READ STEVEN'S BIO		

Steve has been a leader and innovator in financial services and EFT for over 30 years where he and his teams have been instrumental in the development, launch and management of leading edge financial products and services. In his career, Steve has held executive roles at First Data, MasterCard, Cirrus, Pulse EFT Network and RewardsNOW, Inc where he was President and CEO.
Steve assumed his current role with Augeo’s acquisition of RewardsNOW in April, 2015. As President of Augeo’s CLO business unit, he leads all aspects of the business including the client, merchant and tech initiatives and teams; leveraging his knowledge and experience to develop new approaches and applications for the CLO ecosystem.
Steve has a BS in Business from Northern Arizona, an MBA from the University of Houston, and a Juris Doctorate from DePaul University and is a member of the Connecticut Bar Association. Outside of work he spends his time with his wife Brenda and their four daughters and two granddaughters, and supporting the UCONN basketball program—Go Huskies!























				Jill Yates			




				Head of Strategic Partnerships, Sears Shop Your Way (SYW)			




			READ JILL'S BIO »		

Jill Yates, Director Strategic Partnerships with Shop Your Way, a Sears Holdings Company. In this role, she is focused in strategic partnerships with merchants and third parties spanning a wide variety of verticals in everyday spending categories for Shop Your Way, the largest retail loyalty platform and rewards marketplace in the U.S. With tens of millions of active members that earned Shop Your Way points in the past 12 months, Shop Your Way maintains a massive repository of purchase data and behavior insights. Using its data mining and analytic capabilities, its patented rewards engine, and array of digital and marketing channels, Shop Your Way consistently delivers relevant and engaging messaging to members, which guide and drive their continued purchase behavior.
Prior to joining Shop Your Way, Jill spent the previous 15 years at Inmar and Parago (now Blackhawk Network) in a variety of roles focused on the development and advancement of consumer incentive programs for a wide variety of Fortune 500 consumer packaged goods companies, manufacturers and retailers. Jill is passionate about the betterment of advanced analytics and performance of consumer incentive programs. She remains active in a variety of organizations including Path to Purchase, Shopper Marketing, Brand Activation, and now the Cardlinx Association. Jill received a magna cum laude B.A. from the University of Louisville.


















 Our Team





































				Silvio Tavares			




				President and Founding Chief Executive Officer
[email protected] 




			READ SILVIO'S BIO »		

Silvio Tavares is an experienced CEO, senior executive and thought leader with over 15 years of experience in the digital commerce and payments industry. Mr. Tavares is President and CEO of The CardLinx Association, a leading global trade association for the payments and digital advertising industries. CardLinx founding members include MasterCard, Discover, First Data, Facebook and Microsoft among others.
He was previously SVP and Global Head of Information Products at Visa Inc. where he led a business unit generating several hundred million dollars in annual sales and successfully launched key new industry leading products in the areas of payment fraud detection, digital marketing and merchant loyalty. Mr. Tavares joined Visa from First Data, where he was Senior Vice President and Global Head of Information and Analytics. At First Data, he patented and launched First Data’s U.S. macro-economic spending indicator. He began his career at AT&T where he authored one of the earliest business method patents for web-based payments. He has authored over fifteen granted or pending patents in the fields of digital commerce, electronic payments and payments analytics.
Mr. Tavares earned a Juris Doctor degree from the Boston University School of Law (Oxford University Program), an MBA from Boston College and a Bachelor of Science Degree in Electrical and Computer Engineering from Tufts University.























				Sabine Brunthaler			




				Head of the CardLinx European Advisory Board
[email protected] 




			READ SABINE'S BIO »		

Sabine Brunthaler has longstanding, international experience in client-facing advisory roles in professional B2B services providing strategic business support to senior leaders of large and mid-sized global organizations. Most recently with Boyden Executive Search, Sabine was the Lead Partner for Finance and Life Sciences in Switzerland. Additionally, as a committee member of the British-Swiss Chamber of Commerce, she helped member organizations grow in the UK and continental Europe.
Before that, Sabine was CEB’s Director Member Services for their European Finance Practice offering best practice research for management strategies and serving over 150 of Europe’s leading organizations across industries. Her earlier experiences include working for CEB’s IT Practice in new member acquisition, developing marketing strategies for an American software company as well as managing a team of 150 trainers in adult education.
She holds a humanities degree from the University of Vienna and an Austrian diploma in training management. Sabine received her marketing qualifications in the UK with the Chartered Institute of Marketing. Her MBA at London Guildhall University (now London Metropolitan University) allowed her to analyze consulting needs for human resources, information technology and finance in organizations across Europe, an area of additional research for the past two years. Sabine is fluent in German, English, and French.























				Ming Lacey			




				Public Relations Director
[email protected] 




			READ MING'S BIO »		

Ming Lacey is the PR Director of The CardLinx Association.
She directs media outreach and strategy, manages social media engagement, explores strategic partnerships and identifies conference and journalist interviews/ speaking opportunities for CardLinx and its members.
Ming’s communications career began in New York City as the PR and Communications Manager for The Reserve, a money fund company. After managing crisis and triage communications at The Reserve, Ming joined Rubenstein Associates as Assistant Vice President in the financial and legal group where she helped financial services institutions, law firms and non-profit organizations to amplify their messages to the business media. Following a move to Portland, Oregon, Ming worked at LANE PR as Account Director overseeing their largest agency accounts with regional community banks and financial institutions.
Prior to her work in public relations, Ming started her career in the financial services industry as a portfolio assistant at Alliance Bernstein managing municipal bond funds. Then she worked at Citigroup in Hong Kong and New York for five years in varying capacities in the Corporate Realty Services and Global Transaction Services divisions where she focused on marketing, branding and internal communications. Ming is a graduate of the University of Chicago and received a B.A. in Economics.























				Ester Shin			




				Member Manager
[email protected] 




			READ ESTER'S BIO »		

Ester supports the enrollment of new members and member relations for The CardLinx Association, including outreach and registration of new members and ongoing management and support of existing members.























				Catherine Lee			




				Meeting Manager
[email protected] 




			READ CATHERINE'S BIO »		

Catherine (Cathie) organizes CardLinx forums worldwide, which entails venue selection, marketing, logistics, sponsorships, catering, transportation and speaker liaison for each event.


























