Executive Profile
Silvio   Tavares  Independent Director, CPI Card Group Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships45$51,252
Background

		Mr. Silvio Tavares serves as the President and Chief Executive Officer of The CardLinx Association. Prior to CardLinx, Mr. Tavares held two important leadership roles at Visa Inc. and First Data Corporation. He led Visa’s global information products business that included Risk Products such as Visa’s participation in EMVco. Prior to Visa, Mr. Tavares served as Senior Vice President of Information & Analytics Solutions at First Data Corporation. Mr. Tavares served as ... the Head of Investor Relations and Senior Vice President of First Data Corp. since January 18, 2007. Mr. Tavares served as Chief Executive Officer of RedstoneConnect Plc. Prior to First Data, Mr. Tavares served with the Corporate Executive Board Co., in Washington, D.C. He served as a Director of Corporate Finance and Head of U.K. Technology Banking team at ABN AMRO Hoare Govett in London. Before ABN AMRO, he was associated with Shearman & Sterling's corporate securities law practice in London. Mr. Tavares served as Senior Director & Practice Manager of Investor Relations Roundtable, as well as Senior Director for Chief Financial Officer Executive Board. He has been an Independent Director of CPI Card Group Inc. since October 3, 2016. Mr. Tavares is a member of the New York Bar. Mr. Tavares holds a Juris Doctor Degree from Boston University Law School, an M.B.A from Boston College and a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from Tufts University.Read Full Background




